 We used these relationships to find candidate DNA modifications, by identifying entities related to the core nucleobases, which we represent by their symbols: {A,C,G,T,U}. We included uracil, since many of its descendants in the ontology are modifications of thymine (CHEBI:17821, which is equivalent to 5-methyluracil), and are not annotated as descendants of thymine itself. For each of these bases, we imported all entities that are annotated in the ontology as a child of one of these bases, via the F\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
