				\begin{document}$$\mathcal {F}$$\end{document} has functional parent relationship. ChEBI ranks entities based on their degree of curation. We only imported entities with the highest rating—three stars—indicating manual curation by ChEBI. Whenever possible, we only included entities as nitrogenous bases (nucleobases). If ChEBI did not have the nucleobase, we then selected the nucleoside form and finally, if necessary, the nucleotide. These imported bases formed the candidate set of modifications (the unverified set), from which we created a curated set of DNA modifications (the verified set).

